theorem Topology.interior_nonempty_of_dense_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h_dense : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X)) :
    (interior A).Nonempty := by
  classical
  by_cases hInt : (interior A).Nonempty
  · exact hInt
  · -- If `interior A` were empty, its closure would also be empty,
    -- contradicting the density hypothesis.
    have hIntEmpty : interior A = (∅ : Set X) :=
      (Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty).1 hInt
    have hClEmpty : closure (interior A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa [hIntEmpty, closure_empty]
    have h_univ_empty : (Set.univ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
      simpa using (Eq.trans h_dense.symm hClEmpty)
    -- But `Set.univ` is certainly nonempty.
    have h_nonempty_empty : (∅ : Set X).Nonempty := by
      simpa [h_univ_empty] using (Set.nonempty_univ : (Set.univ : Set X).Nonempty)
    rcases h_nonempty_empty with ⟨x, hx⟩
    exact hx.elim

theorem Set.nonempty_univ {α : Type*} : (Set.univ : Set α).Nonempty := by
  simp

theorem Set.nonempty_univ {α : Type*} [h : Nonempty α] :
    (Set.univ : Set α).Nonempty := by
  classical
  rcases h with ⟨x⟩
  exact ⟨x, by simp⟩
